Book Peter Boneparth for a Speaking Engagement
Businesses, Non-profit organizations, event planners and companies across the country have worked closely with our booking agents to hire Peter Boneparth for a speaking engagements, guest appearances, product endorsements and corporate events. Many of those same clients have continued to turn to our speakers bureau as we can easily align Peter Boneparth‚Äôs availability with their upcoming seminar, gala, annual conference, corporate function, and grand opening. Our close relationship with Peter Boneparth‚Äôs  booking agent and management team further enables us to provide inquiring clients with Peter Boneparth‚Äôs speaking fee and appearance cost.
If your goal is to hire Peter Boneparth to be your next keynote speaker or to be the next brand ambassador our celebrity speakers bureau can assist. If Peter Boneparth‚Äôs booking fee is outside your companies budget or your unable to align with his appearance availability, our booking agents can provide you a list of talent that aligns with your event theme, budget and event date.
					

					Peter Boneparth serves as Chief Executive Officer at Women's Moderate Apparel Group. Previously, he served as Chief Executive Officer and President at Jones Apparel Group Inc. from March 2002 to December 7, 2007 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from 1999 to December 7, 2007. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Jones Moderate Division from July 2001 to March 2002. Mr. Boneparth was employed at McNaughton Apparel Group Inc. and served as its Chief Executive Officer from June 1999 to July 12, 2007, President from April 1997 to January 2002, and Chief Operating Officer from April 1997. Prior to that, he served as an Executive Vice President and Senior Managing Director of Investment Banking at Rodman & Renshaw, Inc. from March 28, 1995 to April 1997 and Managing Director of Investment Banking at Mabon Securities Corp. from May 1989 to March 1995. He was a Senior Advisor at Irving Place Capital since February 2009 and focused on retail and apparel sectors. He is also the Chairman of J Brand. He has been a Director of Kohl's Corp. since May 1, 2008, Rodman & Renshaw Capital Group Inc. since April 25, 1995 and JetBlue Airways Corporation since December 11, 2008. Mr. Boneparth also serves as a Member of the Board of Directors of Marissa Christina, Inc. He previously served as a Member of the Board of Directors of Mcnaughton Apparel Group Inc. joining in March 1997 and Jones Apparel Group Inc. from 2001 to July 12, 2007. Mr. Boneparth also served as the Chairman of McNaughton Apparel Group Inc. from January 2001. He received a J.D. degree from the University of Virginia and a B.S., phi beta kappa, from the University of North Carolina.
				


