According to a financial filing yesterday, Mr. Boneparth is leaving the company with stock options and payments through March 2009 that total nearly $17 million.
Photo






Wesley Card was named chief executive of Jones Apparel.


A public relations firm for Jones declined to make Mr. Boneparth or Mr. Card available for comment.A former investment banker, Mr. Boneparth, 47, spent much of his six years at Jones diversifying its clothing offerings through acquisitions, including a hostile takeover of the Maxwell Shoe Company, the purchase of Gloria Vanderbilt and, later, Barneys New York. Mr. Boneparth also famously took Polo Ralph Lauren to court in 2003 because of a dispute regarding a licensing deal.In 2004, when Jones bought Barneys for $400 million, Moody‚Äôs Investors Service downgraded the company‚Äôs debt rating and several analysts downgraded Jones stock. Now, that purchase has proved to be a lucrative investment.
